Installation_Description:
The stainless steel AISI-304 tank involved in the accident (labelled
D-103) had a nominal volumetric capacity of 55.15 m3, a diameter of 2.5
metres and was 8 metres long. It was containing about 40 tonnes of a
mixture of cyclohexanone (55%) and dimethoate (45%). The tank was
nitrogen blanketed under automatic pressure control. During the loading
phase nitrogen, contaminated with volatile substances from the tank,
was sent to the incinerator whilst, during the unloading phase, pure
nitrogen was sent to the tank from a centralized nitrogen storage.
Further the tank was equipped with a vent having a water seal. The
nitrogen pressure was reduced to 200 mm of water for tank blanketing.
When the accident occurred the plant was out of service because the
company had not the authorization for its production.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
